    <p>NPR's Howard Berkes reports on this mix of comedy and competition. </p>
    <p>HOWARD BERKES: The bankrupt bank left a $300,000 hole in U.S. Speedskating's ice just as the big push to next month's Olympics began. Then came the phone call from New York and the November 2nd cablecast of "The Colbert Report." </p>
    <p>(Soundbite of TV show, "The Colbert Report") </p>
